[00:00:00]Lesson 45 Of men and galaxies\n
[au:]人和星系\n
[00:07.56]First listen and then answer the following question.\n
[au:]听录音,然后回答以下问题.\n
[00:11.37]What is the most influential factor in any human society?\n
[au:]在任何一个人类社团当中,最具影响力的因素是什么?\n
[00:17.01]In man's early days, competition with other creatures must have been critical.\n
[au:]在人类早期,人类与其他生物的竞争一定是必不可少的.\n
[00:24.24]But this phase of our development is now finished.\n
[au:]但这个发展阶段已经结束.\n
[00:28.38]Indeed,we lack practice and experience nowadays in dealing with primitive conditions.\n
[au:]确实,我们今天缺乏对付原始环境的实践和经验.\n
[00:34.81]I am sure that,without modern weapons,\n
[au:]我断定,如果没有现代化的武器,\n
[00:38.25]I would make a very poor show of disputing the ownership of a cave with a bear,\n
[au:]要我和一只熊去争洞穴,我会出洋相的,\n
[00:43.31]and in this I do not think that I stand alone.\n
[au:]我也相信,出洋相者并非我一人.\n
[00:47.40]The last creature to compete with man was the mosquito.\n
[au:]能与人竞争的生物最后只有蚊子了,\n
[00:51.96]But even the mosquito has been subdued by attention to drainage and by chemical sprays.\n
[au:]然而即使蚊子,也由于我们注意清理污水和喷洒化学药品而被制服了.\n
[00:58.26]Competition between ourselves,person against person,\n
[au:]然而人类之间的竞争,人与人,\n
[01:02.92]community against community,still persists,however;\n
[au:]团体与团体,依然在进行着,\n
[01:06.97]and it is as fierce as it ever was.\n
[au:]而且和以前一样激烈.\n
[01:10.11]But the competition of man against man is not the simple process envisioned in biology.\n
[au:]但是,人与人的竞争并不像生物学中想象的那样是一个简单过程.\n
[01:16.71]It is not a simple competition,\n
[au:]它已不是简单的、\n
[01:19.84]for a fixed amount of food determined by the physical environment,\n
[au:]由物质环境所决定的、为了争得有限食物而进行的竞争了,\n
[01:23.82]because the environment that determines our evolution,\n
[au:]因为决定我们进化环境的主要方面,\n
[01:26.65]is no longer essentially physical.\n
[au:]已不再是物质.\n
[01:29.40]Our environment is chiefly conditoned by the things we believe.\n
[au:]我们的环境由我们信仰的东西所决定.\n
[01:33.98]Morocco and California are bits of the Earth in very similar latitudes,\n
[au:]摩洛哥和加利福尼亚是地球上纬度极其相似的两个地方,\n
[01:39.64]both on the west coasts of continents with similar climates,\n
[au:]都在各自大陆的西海岸,气候相似,aa\n
[01:44.71]and probably with rather similar natural resources.\n
[au:]自然资源也可能相似.\n
[01:48.38]Yet their present development is wholly different,\n
[au:]但是,这两个地方目前的发展程度完全不一样.\n
[01:52.08]not so much because of different people even,\n
[au:]这倒不是因为人民不同,\n
[01:54.84]but because of the di- fferent thoughts that exist in the minds of their inhabitants.\n
[au:]而是由于居民头脑中的思想不同.\n
[01:59.80]This is the point I wish to emphasize.\n
[au:]这就是我要强调的论点.\n
[02:04.04]The most important factor in our environment is the state of our own minds.\n
[au:]我们环境中最重要的因素就是我们的思想状况.\n
[02:09.61]It is well known that where the white man has invaded a primitive culture,\n
[au:]众所周知,凡是白人侵入原始文化的地方,\n
[02:15.81]the most destructive effects have come not from physical weapons but from ideas.\n
[au:]破坏作用最大的不是杀人的武器,而是思想.\n
[02:21.93]Ideas are dangerous.\n
[au:]思想是危险的.\n
[02:24.43]The Holy Office knew this full well when it caused heretics to be burned in days gone by.\n
[au:]宗教法庭对此是非常清楚的,因此从前它总是把异教徒烧死.\n
[02:31.17]Indeed,the concept of free speech only exists in our modern society,\n
[au:]的确,言论自由的概念只存在于我们现代社会中,\n
[02:37.14]because when you are inside a community,\n
[au:]因为当你生活在一个社团当中时,\n
