[03:46.71]that twenty or thirty pages of ideas and information,\n
[au:]即相信三三十页材料中的思想和情报,\n
[03:50.40]would be capable of turning the present- day world upside down, or even destroying it.\n
[au:]会使当今的世界天翻地覆,甚至毁灭这个世界.\n
[03:56.59]I have often tried to conceive of what those pages might contain,\n
[au:]我常常试图想象这些纸上所写的东西,\n
[04:01.46]but of course I cannot do so,\n
[au:]不过我是做不到的,\n
[04:03.80]because I am a prisoner of the present-day world,just as all of you are.\n
[au:]因为我和你们大家一样,是当今世界上的凡人.\n
[04:09.24]We cannot think outside the particular patterns that our bra- ins are conditioned to,\n
